# Scripted principal for the first-run-interview eval (hermetic, deterministic).
# A fully SYNTHETIC person — zero real-network / PII data. The eval feeds these as
# the answers a live human would give the CoS during first-run-interview.md, so the
# run stays reproducible with no human in the loop. Sourced by run-real-path.sh.
#
# (Deliberately NOT the operator: this is "Jordan", an invented indie dev. If any real
# identity appears here, that's a bug — the whole point is the public repo never
# sees real data.)

# 1. Who are you?
PRIN_NAME="Jordan Rivera"
PRIN_ADDRESS="Jordan"
PRIN_TZ="America/Chicago"
PRIN_ONELINER="Indie developer building a task-tracking SaaS."

# 2. What are you working on?  (repo|one-line|owner ; semicolon-separated)
PRIN_REPOS="taskflow|the SaaS backend (API + jobs)|jordan;taskflow-web|the web client|jordan"

# 3. Standing priorities  (semicolon-separated; 2-4)
PRIN_PRIORITIES="Ship the taskflow private beta;Keep CI green on main;Weekly changelog to beta users"

# 4. Who else is around?  collaborators (name|how they fit) and agents (name|what they own)
PRIN_COLLABORATORS="Sam Ortiz|product designer, reviews UX"
PRIN_AGENTS="taskflow-agent|owns the taskflow backend repo"

# 5. What should I watch?  channels (multi-select) + quiet hours
PRIN_CHANNELS="email,calendar"
PRIN_QUIET="22:00-08:00 America/Chicago"

# 6. How do you like to be kept in the loop?
PRIN_PUSH="yes"
PRIN_STYLE="terse + a link for depth"
PRIN_NEVER="Don't email customers or deploy to prod without asking first."
